Definition: bright with a steady but subdued shining
Example: from the plane we saw the city below agleam with lights; the gleaming brass on the altar; Nereids beneath the nitid moon
Synonyms: gleaming, nitid, bright, with, a, steady, but, subdued, shining, from, the, plane, we, saw, city, below, lights, brass, on, altar, Nereids, beneath, moon
Category: adj.all
